<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><title>All or nothing</title>
<lyrics>[V1]
 When you see a child who dies
 God is guilty
 If a newborn baby comes alive
 You thank the doctor
 If God is almighty you say
 Why is there hunger and strain
 But you throw away your food
 When you're done with your dinner
 Why?

[V2]
 If you see an abandoned dog
 You blame God for him
 But a dog could save a life
 What a hero!

[V3]
 Oh God is all or nothing
 Oh He is everything in our lives
 Oh the beginning and the end
 He is</lyrics>
<hymn_number>3779</hymn_number>
<author>Ashlot</author>
</song>